1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,200
Hello everyone and welcome to EnglishPod.
大家好，欢迎收听EnglishPod。

2
00:00:03,200 --> 00:00:04,280
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

3
00:00:04,280 --> 00:00:06,800
My name is Kathryn and it's the holiday season.
我是Kathryn，现在是节日季。

4
00:00:06,800 --> 00:00:10,560
Today we have a lesson all about a special December holiday.
今天我们有一节课，全部关于一个特别的十二月节日。

5
00:00:10,560 --> 00:00:11,560
That's right.
没错。

6
00:00:11,560 --> 00:00:16,960
We are getting close to Christmas and of course today we are going to talk about Christmas
我们离圣诞节越来越近了，当然今天我们要聊聊圣诞节

7
00:00:16,960 --> 00:00:21,800
in the United States and some of the typical traditions that you see over there.
在美国以及那里的一些典型传统。

8
00:00:21,800 --> 00:00:22,800
That's right.
没错。

9
00:00:22,800 --> 00:00:26,760
So we're going to be looking at a family as they wait for Christmas morning to arrive.
所以我们要看一个家庭等待圣诞早晨到来的情景。

10
00:00:26,760 --> 00:00:30,160
If you don't know what that is, don't worry, you'll hear us talk about it in a moment.
如果你不知道那是什么，别担心，一会儿你会听到我们谈论它。

11
00:00:30,160 --> 00:00:38,880
But first let's listen to our dialogue.
但首先，我们来听一下对话。

12
00:00:38,880 --> 00:00:40,440
What are you doing awake?
你怎么醒着？

13
00:00:40,440 --> 00:00:41,940
I can't sleep.
我睡不着。

14
00:00:41,940 --> 00:00:42,940
But it's almost midnight.
但都快午夜了。

15
00:00:42,940 --> 00:00:43,940
Exactly.
正是。

16
00:00:43,940 --> 00:00:46,940
I'm too excited for Christmas morning.
我对圣诞早晨太兴奋了。

17
00:00:46,940 --> 00:00:50,120
Also, I thought I heard Santa.
还有，我好像听到圣诞老人了。

18
00:00:50,120 --> 00:00:51,120
Really?
真的吗？

19
00:00:51,120 --> 00:00:52,120
How do you know it was Santa?
你怎么知道是圣诞老人？

20
00:00:52,120 --> 00:00:57,280
Well, I heard that naughty boys and girls get coal in their stockings so I thought I'd
嗯，我听说淘气的孩子会在袜子里得到煤块，所以我想

21
00:00:57,280 --> 00:00:59,600
be nice and make Santa cookies.
表现好一点，给圣诞老人做饼干。

22
00:00:59,600 --> 00:01:01,560
I even left out some milk.
我还留了一些牛奶。

23
00:01:01,560 --> 00:01:05,600
I heard someone in the kitchen eating the cookies so I came downstairs.
我听到有人在厨房吃饼干，就下楼来了。

24
00:01:05,600 --> 00:01:06,600
Hmm.
嗯。

25
00:01:06,600 --> 00:01:11,440
Well, I know that Santa won't come down the chimney with you hiding behind the tree spying
嗯，我知道圣诞老人不会在你躲在树后偷看他的时候

26
00:01:11,440 --> 00:01:12,440
on him.
从烟囱下来。

27
00:01:12,440 --> 00:01:13,440
Really?
真的吗？

28
00:01:13,440 --> 00:01:14,440
Really.
真的。

29
00:01:14,440 --> 00:01:16,520
Let's go back upstairs and get back to bed.
我们回楼上，上床睡觉吧。

30
00:01:16,520 --> 00:01:18,720
That way we can let Santa do his job.
这样我们就能让圣诞老人做他的工作了。

31
00:01:18,720 --> 00:01:21,360
Then when you wake up, it will be Christmas already.
等你醒来时，就已经是圣诞节了。

32
00:01:21,360 --> 00:01:22,360
Okay.
好吧。

33
00:01:22,360 --> 00:01:29,240
Hey, honey, is that you?
嘿，亲爱的，是你吗？

34
00:01:29,240 --> 00:01:30,360
Don't eat all the cookies.
别把饼干都吃光了。

35
00:01:30,360 --> 00:01:32,400
I want some too.
我也想吃一些。

36
00:01:32,400 --> 00:01:35,640
Alright, we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

37
00:01:35,640 --> 00:01:41,960
So now let's take a look at some language on Language Takeaway.
现在让我们在“语言要点”环节看看一些语言点。

38
00:01:41,960 --> 00:01:43,480
Language Takeaway.
语言要点。

39
00:01:43,480 --> 00:01:47,840
Okay, I just said it but here's that phrase again.
好的，我刚说了，但这里再提一下这个短语。

40
00:01:47,840 --> 00:01:49,160
Christmas morning.
圣诞早晨。

41
00:01:49,160 --> 00:01:50,160
That's right.
没错。

42
00:01:50,160 --> 00:01:54,760
So Christmas morning is December 25th in the morning, right?
所以圣诞早晨是12月25日的早晨，对吧？

43
00:01:54,760 --> 00:01:55,760
That's right.
没错。

44
00:01:55,760 --> 00:01:56,760
Okay.
好的。

45
00:01:56,760 --> 00:02:01,120
Okay, so the tradition is that small children will wake up early and run downstairs and
好的，传统是小孩子会早起跑下楼，

46
00:02:01,120 --> 00:02:04,280
they will find Christmas presents under the Christmas tree.
在圣诞树下找到圣诞礼物。

47
00:02:04,280 --> 00:02:07,120
And so this is the Christmas morning tradition.
这就是圣诞早晨的传统。

48
00:02:07,120 --> 00:02:11,080
Many countries, they celebrate Christmas on Christmas Eve, the 24th, right?
很多国家在圣诞前夜，也就是24日庆祝圣诞节，对吧？

49
00:02:11,080 --> 00:02:17,400
Alright, so Christmas Eve is December 24th, Christmas Day or if it's in the morning, Christmas
好的，所以圣诞前夜是12月24日，圣诞节或如果是早晨，圣诞早晨

50
00:02:17,400 --> 00:02:20,240
morning is December 25th.
是12月25日。

51
00:02:20,240 --> 00:02:25,920
And as you said, kids come downstairs or go to where the Christmas tree is to look for
就像你说的，孩子们下楼或去圣诞树那里找

52
00:02:25,920 --> 00:02:29,880
their presents that Santa came and left for them.
圣诞老人来给他们留下的礼物。

53
00:02:29,880 --> 00:02:30,880
That's right.
没错。

54
00:02:30,880 --> 00:02:35,720
So the idea, the story is that Santa comes at night, late at night and brings presents
所以这个想法，这个故事是圣诞老人晚上来，深夜来，给孩子们

55
00:02:35,720 --> 00:02:37,000
for the children.
带礼物。

56
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:40,840
And when the children wake up, they see the presents but Santa has already gone.
当孩子们醒来时，他们看到礼物，但圣诞老人已经走了。

57
00:02:40,840 --> 00:02:47,440
So Santa is a man, he's kind of a mythical figure with a big white beard and a red outfit
所以圣诞老人是一个男人，他有点像神话人物，有大白胡子和红色套装

58
00:02:47,440 --> 00:02:48,920
and a red hat.
和红帽子。

59
00:02:48,920 --> 00:02:49,920
Right.
对。

60
00:02:49,920 --> 00:02:54,120
So his name is Santa Claus or just Santa.
所以他的名字是Santa Claus或简称Santa。

61
00:02:54,120 --> 00:02:58,920
There are many, many different names for Santa in different cultures and different countries.
在不同文化和不同国家，圣诞老人有很多很多不同的名字。

62
00:02:58,920 --> 00:03:04,200
Yeah, some people like to call him Saint Nick or Saint Nicholas but most people will call
是的，有些人喜欢叫他Saint Nick或Saint Nicholas，但大多数人会叫

63
00:03:04,200 --> 00:03:05,960
him Santa in America.
他Santa，在美国。

64
00:03:05,960 --> 00:03:06,960
That's right.
没错。

65
00:03:06,960 --> 00:03:13,080
So this is what happens or part of what happens during Christmas Eve and Christmas Day.
所以这就是圣诞前夜和圣诞节期间发生的事或部分事。

66
00:03:13,080 --> 00:03:18,400
And usually also, boys and girls will find our stockings that will be filled with candy
通常，男孩和女孩还会发现我们的袜子，里面会装满糖果

67
00:03:18,400 --> 00:03:20,320
or small toys as well.
或小玩具。

68
00:03:20,320 --> 00:03:21,320
That's right.
没错。

69
00:03:21,320 --> 00:03:24,240
Stockings are basically socks.
袜子基本上就是袜子。

70
00:03:24,240 --> 00:03:28,800
But these are special socks that you don't wear, you hang them and a lot of people like
但这些都是你不穿的特别袜子，你挂起来，很多人喜欢

71
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:30,880
to put them on the fireplace.
把它们放在壁炉上。

72
00:03:30,880 --> 00:03:32,720
They hang them from the fireplace.
他们把它们挂在壁炉上。

73
00:03:32,720 --> 00:03:35,400
And like you said, Marco, they're filled with sweets.
就像你说的，Marco，它们装满了糖果。

74
00:03:35,400 --> 00:03:40,520
The story says that boys and girls who are nice get good things like sweets and toys
故事说，表现好的男孩和女孩会得到好东西，比如糖果和玩具，

75
00:03:40,520 --> 00:03:43,720
and boys and girls who are naughty get coal.
而淘气的男孩和女孩会得到煤块。

76
00:03:43,720 --> 00:03:44,720
Coal.
煤块。

77
00:03:44,720 --> 00:03:49,960
So that's that black material that we use to make a barbecue for example.
就是那种我们用来做烧烤之类的黑色材料。

78
00:03:49,960 --> 00:03:50,960
Yeah, exactly.
是的，没错。

79
00:03:50,960 --> 00:03:53,640
It's very dirty and it's not something you want in your stocking.
它很脏，不是你想要的袜子里的东西。

80
00:03:53,640 --> 00:03:54,640
Okay.
好的。

81
00:03:54,640 --> 00:03:55,640
That's right.
没错。

82
00:03:55,640 --> 00:03:57,240
So that's what we get in our stockings.
所以这就是我们袜子里得到的东西。

83
00:03:57,240 --> 00:04:02,840
And now when the small boy and his father were talking, they were saying that he should
现在，当那个小男孩和他父亲说话时，他们说他应该

84
00:04:02,840 --> 00:04:07,640
go back to bed and not hide behind the tree.
回到床上，不要躲在树后面。

85
00:04:07,640 --> 00:04:11,160
So if they're in the living room or they're downstairs in the house, what tree do they
所以如果他们在客厅或楼下，他们有什么树？

86
00:04:11,160 --> 00:04:12,160
have?
有？

87
00:04:12,160 --> 00:04:14,640
We're not talking about a big real tree outside.
我们说的不是外面的大真树。

88
00:04:14,640 --> 00:04:17,560
We're talking about the Christmas tree.
我们说的是圣诞树。

89
00:04:17,560 --> 00:04:20,200
But you know, it's a long phrase, the Christmas tree.
但你知道，圣诞树是个很长的短语。

90
00:04:20,200 --> 00:04:21,800
We don't have to say it that way.
我们不必那样说。

91
00:04:21,800 --> 00:04:25,200
When we have a Christmas tree inside the house, we can just call it the tree.
当我们在屋里有一棵圣诞树时，我们可以直接叫它树。

92
00:04:25,200 --> 00:04:26,200
Okay.
好的。

93
00:04:26,200 --> 00:04:31,160
And the Christmas tree, as many of you may have seen already, is a pine tree usually
圣诞树，你们很多人可能已经见过，通常是松树，

94
00:04:31,160 --> 00:04:34,720
and you put decorations on it and the presents go under it.
你会在上面挂装饰品，礼物放在下面。

95
00:04:34,720 --> 00:04:35,720
That's right.
没错。

96
00:04:35,720 --> 00:04:41,040
So you might hear this phrase, there are presents under the tree or there are many nice presents
所以你可能会听到这个短语：树下有礼物，或者树下有很多漂亮的礼物。

97
00:04:41,040 --> 00:04:42,040
under the tree.
树下有很多漂亮的礼物。

98
00:04:42,040 --> 00:04:44,640
That means there are lots of nice presents under the Christmas tree.
这意味着圣诞树下有很多漂亮的礼物。

99
00:04:44,640 --> 00:04:45,640
That's right.
没错。

100
00:04:45,640 --> 00:04:51,120
And well, the kid wanted to stay behind the tree and spy on Santa Claus.
嗯，那个孩子想躲在树后面偷看圣诞老人。

101
00:04:51,120 --> 00:04:52,120
That's right.
没错。

102
00:04:52,120 --> 00:04:53,800
So this is a verb, to spy.
所以这是一个动词，偷看。

103
00:04:53,800 --> 00:05:00,280
This means to watch someone but to watch them while they don't know that you're watching
意思是观察某人，但在他们不知道你在看的情况下观察他们。

104
00:05:00,280 --> 00:05:01,280
them.
观察他们。

105
00:05:01,280 --> 00:05:02,520
So you're hiding but looking at someone else.
所以你躲着，但看着别人。

106
00:05:02,520 --> 00:05:03,520
Right.
对。

107
00:05:03,520 --> 00:05:04,520
You're spying.
你在偷看。

108
00:05:04,520 --> 00:05:08,320
This is where the noun comes, a spy like James Bond.
这就是名词的来源，间谍，比如詹姆斯·邦德。

109
00:05:08,320 --> 00:05:10,080
James Bond spies.
詹姆斯·邦德是间谍。

110
00:05:10,080 --> 00:05:12,080
He is a very famous spy.
他是个非常著名的间谍。

111
00:05:12,080 --> 00:05:13,080
That's right.
没错。

112
00:05:13,080 --> 00:05:17,280
But in this case, the boy does not want Santa Claus to see him so he is spying on Santa
但在这个情况下，男孩不想让圣诞老人看到他，所以他在偷看圣诞老人。

113
00:05:17,280 --> 00:05:18,280
Claus.
圣诞老人。

114
00:05:18,280 --> 00:05:19,280
All right.
好的。

115
00:05:19,280 --> 00:05:20,280
Very good stuff.
非常好的内容。

116
00:05:20,280 --> 00:05:30,360
Let's listen to the dialogue again and review this vocab.
让我们再听一遍对话，复习这些词汇。

117
00:05:30,360 --> 00:05:31,920
What are you doing awake?
你怎么还没睡？

118
00:05:31,920 --> 00:05:33,420
I can't sleep.
我睡不着。

119
00:05:33,420 --> 00:05:34,420
But it's almost midnight.
但都快午夜了。

120
00:05:34,420 --> 00:05:35,420
Exactly.
正是。

121
00:05:35,420 --> 00:05:38,420
I'm too excited for Christmas morning.
我对圣诞早晨太兴奋了。

122
00:05:38,420 --> 00:05:41,720
Also, I thought I heard Santa.
而且，我好像听到了圣诞老人的声音。

123
00:05:41,720 --> 00:05:42,720
Really?
真的吗？

124
00:05:42,720 --> 00:05:43,720
How do you know it was Santa?
你怎么知道那是圣诞老人？

125
00:05:43,720 --> 00:05:48,240
Well, I heard that naughty boys and girls get coal in their stockings.
嗯，我听说淘气的孩子袜子里会得到煤块。

126
00:05:48,240 --> 00:05:51,080
So I thought I'd be nice and make Santa cookies.
所以我想表现好一点，给圣诞老人做饼干。

127
00:05:51,080 --> 00:05:53,080
I even left out some milk.
我还留了一些牛奶。

128
00:05:53,080 --> 00:05:57,400
I heard someone in the kitchen eating the cookies so I came downstairs.
我听到有人在厨房吃饼干，就下楼了。

129
00:05:57,400 --> 00:05:58,400
Hmm.
嗯。

130
00:05:58,400 --> 00:06:02,920
Well, I know that Santa won't come down the chimney with you hiding behind the tree spying
嗯，我知道如果你躲在树后面偷看圣诞老人，他就不会从烟囱下来。

131
00:06:02,920 --> 00:06:03,920
on him.
偷看他。

132
00:06:03,920 --> 00:06:04,920
Really?
真的吗？

133
00:06:04,920 --> 00:06:05,920
Really.
真的。

134
00:06:05,920 --> 00:06:08,000
Let's go back upstairs and get back to bed.
我们回楼上，回到床上吧。

135
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:09,880
That way we can let Santa do his job.
这样我们就能让圣诞老人做他的工作。

136
00:06:09,880 --> 00:06:15,200
Then when you wake up, it will be Christmas already.
等你醒来时，就已经是圣诞节了。

137
00:06:15,200 --> 00:06:20,720
Hey, honey, is that you?
嘿，亲爱的，是你吗？

138
00:06:20,720 --> 00:06:21,840
Don't eat all the cookies.
别把饼干都吃光了。

139
00:06:21,840 --> 00:06:23,320
I want some too.
我也想吃一些。

140
00:06:23,320 --> 00:06:26,040
All right, we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

141
00:06:26,040 --> 00:06:32,960
So now let's take a look at three phrases on Fluency Builder.
现在让我们看看流利度训练中的三个短语。

142
00:06:32,960 --> 00:06:33,960
Fluency Builder.
流利度训练。

143
00:06:33,960 --> 00:06:34,960
All right.
好的。

144
00:06:34,960 --> 00:06:40,840
So, Marco, there's another great phrase in here that we often use just around Christmas.
所以，马可，这里还有一个很棒的短语，我们通常在圣诞节前后使用。

145
00:06:40,840 --> 00:06:42,880
What is it that Santa Claus does?
圣诞老人做什么？

146
00:06:42,880 --> 00:06:49,560
Well, the way Santa Claus leaves presents for boys and girls is that he will come down
嗯，圣诞老人给孩子们送礼物时，他会从烟囱下来。

147
00:06:49,560 --> 00:06:50,560
the chimney.
从烟囱下来。

148
00:06:50,560 --> 00:06:55,760
We saw that when the dad said, well, Santa Claus won't come down the chimney if you're
我们看到爸爸说，如果你躲在这里树后面，圣诞老人就不会从烟囱下来。

149
00:06:55,760 --> 00:06:57,560
here hiding behind the tree.
躲在这里树后面。

150
00:06:57,560 --> 00:06:58,560
All right.
好的。

151
00:06:58,560 --> 00:07:01,080
So the chimney is part of the fireplace.
所以烟囱是壁炉的一部分。

152
00:07:01,080 --> 00:07:04,840
A fireplace is where you have a fire in your house to keep warm.
壁炉是你在屋里生火取暖的地方。

153
00:07:04,840 --> 00:07:08,080
And the chimney is where the smoke goes to come outside.
烟囱是烟排到外面的地方。

154
00:07:08,080 --> 00:07:09,960
But Santa Claus goes the other way.
但圣诞老人是反方向走的。

155
00:07:09,960 --> 00:07:13,760
He comes down the chimney from the roof into your house.
他从屋顶顺着烟囱进到你的屋里。

156
00:07:13,760 --> 00:07:14,760
That's right.
没错。

157
00:07:14,760 --> 00:07:16,120
And then he leaves the presents.
然后他留下礼物。

158
00:07:16,120 --> 00:07:19,840
So the father said, all right, so, you know, stop spying on Santa.
所以爸爸说，好了，你知道，别再偷看圣诞老人了。

159
00:07:19,840 --> 00:07:23,000
Let's go back upstairs and get back to bed.
我们回楼上，回到床上吧。

160
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:24,000
All right.
好的。

161
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:25,000
Get back to bed.
回床上去。

162
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:28,320
And this is a phrase that you're going to hear parents say a lot to their children.
这是一个你会经常听到父母对孩子说的短语。

163
00:07:28,320 --> 00:07:32,480
So if the children are awake or walking around, you say, get back to bed.
所以如果孩子醒了或者到处走动，你就说，回床上去。

164
00:07:32,480 --> 00:07:34,100
That means go back to sleep.
意思是回去睡觉。

165
00:07:34,100 --> 00:07:35,160
Go back to sleep.
回去睡觉。

166
00:07:35,160 --> 00:07:36,160
